{%- comment -%}
  Reading time estimate — Shopify has no native word-count or reading-time
  object, so this computes one from the article's own content (~200 words/
  minute, a commonly used average) and outputs just the text, e.g. "4 min
  read". Used by both blog-card.liquid and main-article.liquid so the same
  200wpm assumption lives in exactly one place.

  Accepts: content (required): the article's raw content/body HTML.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- liquid
  assign word_count = content | strip_html | split: ' ' | size
  assign minutes = word_count | plus: 199 | divided_by: 200
  assign minutes = minutes | at_least: 1
-%}
{{ 'blog.reading_time' | t: minutes: minutes }}
